# README Architecture Guardrails

- Keep the core flow explicit: image capture in Flutter -> backend proxy -> Gemini -> structured vocabulary result.
- Never document direct Gemini calls from Flutter; `GEMINI_API_KEY` must stay backend-only.
- Preserve API contract for `POST /analyze-image`:
  - Requires `Authorization: Bearer <Firebase ID token>`
  - Request body has `imageBase64` and `mimeType`
  - Response keys stay: `englishWord`, `vietnameseTranslation`, `pronunciationGuide`, `exampleSentence`
- When changing run instructions, keep both local Node and Docker paths accurate.
- Keep naming consistent with project terms: Scan, Result, Vocabulary List, Flashcard (optional).
- Avoid adding undocumented features; if architecture changes, update API and run sections in the same edit.
